e>   Focus quest items</span><hr size=1> All the 4 types of giant toes drop off Gornit in Ocean of Tears.  Don't even think of fighting Gornit at your level, however, Gornit is one of the most heavily camped mobs in the game so if you go to OOT and find out who's camping they should let you hang around and loot a set of toes, unless they are totally greedy.  You can always offer to bank for them cos they will be getting very encumbered.<br>
<br>
For the gems there's little for it than to take the hit on your savings, the gems drop off 40+ mobs like seafury cyclopses and sell to NPCs for over 50pp so it's unlikely that someone will just let you loot one.<br>
<br>
The brooms and shovels etc are rare drops off magicians in Najena.  You'll be lucky to survive long in there at 21, best get a group cos you'll be in there for quite a while.  Lvl 50ish mages have to hunt the same magicians for epic drops, so if you find a senior mage farming Najena, ask if you can tag along.  Can't comment on whether it is easier to get them off Alligators in Feerrott, since that patch was after my time.<br>
<br>
The other bits and pieces like griffin feathers you can find on traders in the zones where they drop if you are patient, especially soon after a patch when the traders have been reset.  The traders on Sister Isle on Ocean of Tears (first stop out of Freeport) can have quite a few bits if you're lucky but the toes can be pricey, best to get friends with the Gornit campers if you're strapped for cash <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Failing all this, try the bazaar, if you hang around long enough you'll find some decent folk who hang onto quest items and sell them for a small amount.  There are, of course, rip-off scum who try to sell at prices that a first time player could not afford. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uflambodius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Flambodius</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#333333>(8/12/02 2:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1042.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Focus quest items</span><hr size=1> I've bought the torch, stein, shovel, and broom-- some of them more than once (made a mistake and turned in the broom instead of the shovel once, and have given items to magician friends).<br>
<br>
The most successful tactic for me has been /auctioning for them in bazaar.  Once I found one in a bazaar search (I think I filtered for Primary but I'm not sure).  But the most successful has been auction.  Usually someone knows someone who has one, or perhaps an alternate character has one.<br>
<br>
I did this starting at level 20, and it was quite expensive for me.  I harvested gargoyle eyes in Ocean of Tears to finance this undertaking.<br>
<br>
I highly recommend getting your torch first if you can, and getting the research components for your 24 fire pet.  My focused 20 firepet outperformed my unfocused 24 earth pet by a wide margin when fighting gargoyles.  Now that I have my 24 fire pet and a torch-- he's fearsome. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ravian>Ravian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#333333>(11/5/02 3:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1042.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Focus quest items</span><hr size=1> I fought for the 4 items from the mages I bought most the other stuff in the bazaar.  Also did some vendor hoping.  Very rewarding quest. <p><img src=http://www.legionoffyre.net/disappearing%20flame.gif><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=425856><b>Ravian Varior</b></a><img src=http://www.legionoffyre.net/disappearing%20flame.gif><br><a href=http://www.legionoffyre.net><b>----{}Legion of Fyer{}---</b></a><br><b>---LVL 47 Erudite Mage---</b><br><a href=http://pub17.ezboard.com/bxegony >----------Xegony----------</a>
