1. Toes - Got all 4 sets from the HElf vendor in OOT where we buy our pet spells. Cost was around 7-9pp each.<br>
2. Griffon feather - Gypsy vendor in NK. Around 10pp.<br>
3. Gargoyle eye - Same lady as in #1. There are Gargoyles in OOT on Spectre Isle. Around 10pp.<br>
4. Mermaid Scale - Had to farm this, couldn't find it in Bazaar or any vendors in OOT. I just took boat from BB and jumped off the first rocks. Killed a single Alluring Siren and she dropped it. No charge <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
5. Broom, shovel, etc. - Looked in Bazaar on and off for 3 days never saw any of these. I pulled at my Wiz and went to Najena. I only did Magicians but somebody in the zone said anything in the zone can drop them. I'm not sure if that's true and I wasn't taking chances. I just did a 3-4 camp cycle - On way into main area there's 1 Mage in the entry area, 1 that stands not far from there by a gate as you're heading to the stairs that take you N, the 3-4 Gobs standing in SE corner (what spawns here changes so you may get 1-3 Magicians in here), heading N from the Gobs (past a black widow) there's another 4-5 spawn Gob camp, and lastly the Crystal Room. I got 2 of the items in Crystal, 1 from one of the Mages on way in, and 1 from the 2 Gob camps.<br>
6. Gems - Found a couple at gem vendor in SH but couldn't find a star ruby or sapphire. Went to Felwithe and checked gem vendors there. Couldn't find either on most of them but the 1 in the bldg just as you zone into SFel had the sapphire and star ruby. Guess they are drop instead of normal vendor sellable. /shrug. Total cost for all (this is with a 110 Cha) and Ally to HElf &amp; Amiably to SH vendors, was around 400pp.<br>
<br>
That's it. Good luck. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=silinye>silinye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(12/1/02 7:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1042.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  re:focus items</span><hr size=1> I just recently completed all four quests and the information i have isn't much different from those posted above =) However, i thought I would add a little bit of my experience:<br>
<br>
It took a few hours to get the broom, shovel and torch to drop in Najena. The items do drop off of any mage in the dungeon - as the broom dropped several times in different locations. It may be easier to camp Rathyl's room/ Mage room - however I would not suggest this unless you have a full group and are level 20+.<br>
<br>
The hardest item for me to get was the stein. I camped Najena mages for over 2 days and it didn't drop once. A higher level ended up giving it to me when it dropped for them. The broom dropped a lot :0 <br>
<br>
I ended up having to buy the gems - which took a week or two of spider silk, bone chip and pelt farming to get the money needed. I killed in lavastorm to get the fire drake scale, and also used the loot from the munsters I killed to go towards the cost of the gems (My mages charisma is fairly low, so if possible get a buff to improve your charisma so buying them doesn't hurt so much). <br>
Also, hunting in guk yeilded atleast 50pp for me - I went there with a friend to camp the froglok tonta knight for the soiled boots (for earthen boots) - wasn't successful, but yeilded a nice sum for a few hours of work.<br>
<br>
I killed in karana during my teens, so I saved every feather dropped from the griffons there to go towards this quest. <br>
<br>
The toes and gargoyle eyes i got very lucky with. I bought the eye in neriak (i'm a de mage) and the toes in the bazaar.  It took some farming on my part to get the cash to do so - as I was also heavily (and perhaps stupidly) spending money on components needed so I could have my level 29 earth pet. What a waste lol :0<br>
<br>
Mermaid scale was very easy, I jumped off of the boat and swam to the isle. Killed two and got a scale right off.  Getting back ON the boat took two tries heehee :0  First time I swam under and then up but wasn't quick enough=) (I was with a friend who cannot gate and needed invis to get through freeport, so we tried to get back together).<br>
<br>
Easiest = mermaid scale and, of course, items bought.<br>
Longest= items from Najena <br>
Ouchiest = cost of gems :0<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bonks>Bonks</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#333333>(12/3/02 1:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerequipmentandquests.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1042.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  They drop of a LOT more than just Mages!!!!</span><hr size=1> In Najena, the 4 main focus quest parts (a shovel, a torch, a stein, a broom) AND any of the 4 Mastery pages for the epic can be dropped by <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>ANY OF THESE SPAWNS</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>a Magician</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
12 spawns and ANY can drop these items.<br>
2 beyond the hidden wall<br>
1 at the main entrance into the 'main area'<br>
1 just beyond the entrance<br>
2 that spawn in with Najena<br>
2 spawn in the crystal room<br>
3 spawn in the left side jail room<br>
1 can spawn in the room ajoined to this (where a named spawns (name elludes me just now)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Dark Boned Skeleton</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
2 spawns (as far as i know <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
these spawn in the room right of the 3 magician room in the jail area, more skeletons are in there but there trash.<br>
Many dispute this, but i promise, as of 29 Nov 2002 these have dropped these, ive seen 2 torches and a shovel and numerous mastery pages.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>a Goblin Magician</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
11 spawn<br>
1 in a tunnel to the left as you enter Najenas water tunnel area (surrounded by ogre guards)<br>
3 in the room to the right of the water tunnel<br>
6 round a camp fire, just behind and up a ramp to the previous 3<br>
and 1 that wanders between the previous 2 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
ALL the goblin spawns can spawn either a warrior, a magician, or a Minoc, the minoc being the highest level<br>
<br>
<br>
I was in Najena with my druid to get these items for a LONG time, then returned as my Mage at 39 to get the broom (which had kept itself too scarce for my liking, but it dropped, eventually <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) and got some kind of drop of all of the above, usually duplicates!<br>
<br>
